	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104144577348961><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=17945&mid=104144577348961>The sword</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=17945&mid=104144577348961#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=200155><span id= >Milin</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 1st 1:56 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yeah, that's pretty much what the reaction was -&nbsp;&nbsp;lots of surprise. :)  (OMG - it proc'd a bard epic sword.  Shut up.  Seriously!)  At the time it was the first one server-wide, and bards from across the servers made mules on Saryrn to come check it out.  We had a fun Gathering of the Bards!  (Hold your jokes please)<br><br>As for the pets, they are not controllable and do not show up on the pet bar.  You can have a charmed pet while these things are popping.  There will be as many up as you can proc in 10 seconds - I've seen four up at one time.  The pets will attack whatever you are currently attacking and will defend against new attackers.  Basically, they seem to work the same way as other swarm pets.<br><br>The pet hits for 51 max, so it's really a 200-400 damage proc on average.<br><br>Anyway, it may not be the best weapon in the expansion, but it is probably the most fun.<br><br>---<br>Impresario Milin<br>Heaven and Earth - www.hneguild.com<br>Saryrn<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan  1 13:36:23 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
